 In the independent double hurdle model, the chance that income (Y) is zero is the product of 
 chance that the hidden/covered up (number or thing that changes) off-farm labour 
 income (Y*) is negative and the chance that 
 Y* is positive. In this case, there is an (fear/stopping of behavior) to 
 carry out the want to join the labour market. 
 As a result, the log chance function for the 
 independent double hurdle model is given by 
 Blundell and Meghir (Blundell and Meghir, 1987, 
